&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Opportunity to lead a veterinary team in a Medical Director role.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnership with Heart + Paw, a leading veterinary community with strong operational support.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Co-ownership option with flexible buy-in starting at $20,000, with ownership up to 49%.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why Heart + Paw and South Peak Veterinary Hospital Clinic Stand Out:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As a Partner Veterinarian, you’ll have the freedom to build the practice culture and clinical protocols you envision. This role offers:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;True Partnership&lt;/strong&gt; – Share in practice decisions and receive semi-annual profit distributions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Ownership Flexibility&lt;/strong&gt; – Buy-in options range from 5-49% with financing assistance if needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Comprehensive Support&lt;/strong&gt; – Receive mentorship and operational guidance from our Heart + Paw community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Focus on Preventive Care&lt;/strong&gt; – Provide leading-edge care with a focus on the human-animal bond and low-stress handling techniques.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Role as Partner Veterinarian:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As the primary leader at South Peak Veterinary Hospital, you will oversee the center’s daily operations, quality of care, and client experience. Responsibilities include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Leading a team to deliver high-quality, client-focused veterinary services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Promoting preventive care and ensuring compliance with veterinary standards and Heart + Paw protocols.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Acting as a role model and brand champion for Heart + Paw within the community.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Guiding and mentoring associate veterinarians and support staff to enhance skills and patient care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Communicating effectively with clients, utilizing technology for telemedicine, texting, and email.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborating with the Center Director to manage team hiring, training, and scheduling.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participating in planning, budgeting, and financial performance reviews, sharing insights with Heart + Paw leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
